.SH "NAME"
Specio::Constraint::ObjectIsa \- A class for constraints which require an object that inherits from a specific class
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
version 0.46
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&    my $type = Specio::Constraint::ObjectIsa\->new(...);
\&    print $type\->class;
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
This is a specialized type constraint class for types which require an object
that inherits from a specific class.
.SH "API"
.IX Header "API"
This class provides all of the same methods as Specio::Constraint::Simple,
with a few differences:
.SS "Specio::Constraint::ObjectIsa\->new( ... )"
.IX Subsection "Specio::Constraint::ObjectIsa->new( ... )"
The \f(CW\*(C`parent\*(C'\fR parameter is ignored if it passed, as it is always set to the
\&\f(CW\*(C`Defined\*(C'\fR type.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`inline_generator\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`constraint\*(C'\fR parameters are also ignored. This
class provides its own default inline generator subroutine reference.
.PP
This class overrides the \f(CW\*(C`message_generator\*(C'\fR default if none is provided.
.PP
Finally, this class requires an additional parameter, \f(CW\*(C`class\*(C'\fR. This must be a
single class name.
.ie n .SS "$object_isa\->class"
.el .SS "\f(CW$object_isa\fP\->class"
.IX Subsection "$object_isa->class"
Returns the class name passed to the constructor.
.SH "ROLES"
.IX Header "ROLES"
This class does the Specio::Constraint::Role::IsaType,
Specio::Constraint::Role::Interface, and Specio::Role::Inlinable roles.
